Project success criteria
Our goal is to have the website fully operational by our deadline without spending any money on it.  If we don’t complete the website by our deadline the project will be considered a failure.  If we can get the main features functional by the deadline it will be considered a success.

1.0 Initiating
	1.1 Identify primary stakeholders
	1.2 Conduct initial meeting
	1.3 Develop communication covenant
	1.4 Prepare business case
2.0 Planning
	2.1 Hold team planning meetings
	2.2 Prepare scope statement
	2.3 Gather initial requirements
		2.3.1 Survey stakeholders
           2.3 Prepare to do list
		2.3.1 Prioritize features and functions
	2.4 Prepare WBS
	2.5 Prepare schedule and costs
		2.5.1 Determine task resources
		2.5.2 Determine task durations
		2.5.3 Prepare Gantt Chart
2.6 Identify, discuss, and prioritize risks

3.1 Establish Technical Framework

3.6 Site Roll out
